==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Blackburnian warbler
<hw>Black*bur"ni*an war"bler</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>. <ety>[Named from Mrs.
<etsep>Blackburn</etsep>, an English lady.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>A beautiful warbler of the United States (<spn>Dendroica
Blackburni⟦ae⟧</spn>). The male is strongly marked with orange, yellow,
and black on the head and neck, and has an orange-yellow
breast.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Blackcap</ent>⟦br⟧
